# Supabase

- **Two clients.** `lib/supabase/server.ts` (cookies, used in Server Components and Server Actions) and `lib/supabase/client.ts` (anon key, browser only). Never import the server client from a Client Component.
- **Service-role key** (`SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`) is for cron/webhook contexts only and lives in `lib/supabase/admin.ts`. Never expose it to the browser bundle. Audit every import.
- **RLS everywhere.** Every table has Row-Level Security enabled and at least one policy. A new table without an RLS policy must not ship. The migration tests verify this.
- **Migrations are source of truth.** Schema changes go in `supabase/migrations/NNNN_slug.sql`. Never use the Supabase dashboard to alter schema in production.
- **Generated types.** Run `pnpm supabase gen types typescript --linked > lib/supabase/database.types.ts` after every migration. Commit the types.

```ts
// GOOD
import type { Database } from "@/lib/supabase/database.types";
const supabase = createClient<Database>();

// BAD — losing column-level types
const supabase = createClient();
```

- **Webhooks** verify Supabase's signing secret before trusting payload.
